<paragraph blockId="54.[828,1467,1413,1469]" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836">
Basonym: 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1157,1413,1437]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[945,1157,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836">Lactobacillus brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1397,1413,1437]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Betabacterium" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="breve">
<emphasis box="[1176,1397,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836">Betabacterium breve</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Orla- Jensen 1919, 175) Bergey 
<emphasis box="[1100,1144,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836">etal</emphasis>
. 1934, 312 (Approved Lists)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[828,1467,1491,1674]" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836">
The species was described in [
<bibRefCitation author="Orla-Jensen S." box="[1166,1182,1491,1515]" journalOrPublisher="Copenhagen: Andr Fred HOst and Son" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836" refId="ref59648" refString="2. Orla-Jensen S. The lactic acid bacteria. Copenhagen: Andr Fred HOst and Son; 1919." title="The lactic acid bacteria" type="book" year="1919">2</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergey DH &amp; Breed RS &amp; Hammer BW &amp; Huntoon FM &amp; Murray EGD" box="[1196,1241,1491,1515]" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836" refId="ref72338" refString="289. Bergey DH, Breed RS, Hammer BW, Huntoon FM, Murray EGD et al. Bergey's Manual of Determinative Bacteriology, 4 th ed. Baltimore: The Williams &amp; Wilkins Co; 1934." type="book" year="1934">289</bibRefCitation>
]. Strains of 
<taxonomicName box="[1374,1467,1491,1515]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[1374,1467,1491,1515]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836">L. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
widely occur in vegetable and cereal fermentations and as beer-spoilage organisms and were also isolated from insects. Niche adaptation is mediated by acquisition of plasmids [
<bibRefCitation author="Fraunhofer ME &amp; Geissler AJ &amp; Behr J &amp; Vogel RF" box="[834,880,1618,1642]" pageId="54" pageNumber="2836" pagination="37 - 47" refId="ref72377" refString="290. Fraunhofer ME, Geissler AJ, Behr J, Vogel RF. Comparative genomics of Lactobacillus brevis reveals a significant plasmidome overlap of brewery and insect isolates. Curr Microbiol 2019; 76: 37 - 47." type="journal article" year="2019">290</bibRefCitation>
]. The genome size of the type strain is 2.47 Mbp. The mol% G+C content of DNAis 46.0.
</paragraph>
